column5: Well my annual trip is out of the way again for the year and I can't wait for the next one all ready. I had another great adventure with lots of fish caught and a great visit with friends I only get to spend time with once a year cause of distance we live apart now. We hit great weather for the week and fishing was consistent every day.  I'll let the pics tell the rest of the story.  Home for 5 days, not too rough eh!   The view from camp   Me with some fish fry keepers   Some visitors    sunset from the camp   Time to go home   The gang
Looks like a great time Smokey. Thanks for sharing..
Thanks for that, brings back memories! I paddled up the Atwood system to Felsia then up the Witchwood River entering the lake. That's some real nice country up there!

Glad to hear you had another good fly-in, Mike.  It won't be long before the next one ... just a long winters nap.  Nice pics ... I see you are getting older .... really roughing it in that log tent. LOL  Don
Great pics and report. Must have been tough having to rough it in that beautiful cabin for 5 days. Thanks Smokey.  Cheers, 1leg
